Class: module:neo4j-query-object

module:neo4j-query-object

This class handles "Query Objects", an object that holds a single query with configuration on how to handle the query along with a method to issue a proper callback on a parsed or unparsed query response.

Constructor

new module:neo4j-query-object(objopt)

A query and its configuration and proper callback

Creates an instance of this class, one instance per query. Upon creation a promise will be generated which will be finalized when issued with the result.

Once a promise is issued a new one will be generated in case the instance is used again.

(private) generatePromise() → {undefined}

Destroy the current promise and create a new one

Destroy the current promise and create a new one, should never be called explicitly, only intended and needed to be called right after the current promise has been executed.

issuePromise(erropt, objopt) → {Promise}

issue promise on query

Pass information from the result that will determine whether the promise should be rejected or resolved based on err being filled out or not.

The promise will then be resolved or rejected and a new promise will take its place in case this instance is desired to be re-used in some way.

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
err any <optional>

Error from query, if any
obj module:neo4j-query-object~queryResultObj <optional>
 {}

The result object to provide

"queryObj" property should not be provided and will be ignored if done so, that property is set by the method and references this class.
